title: NB's Beastiary
author: grifoelmes
pages:
#- Novo Blyat's Beastiary§0
§0
§0By: grifoelmes§0
§0+++++++++++++++++++§0
§0
§0This books is based off of my experiences with the creatures found in this peninsula - Which belongs to me at the time of writing this book.§0
§0
§0God bless us all.
#- I: Clouds§0
§0This may sound dumb, but the clouds in this place do appear to have intentions, specially in the high peaks of this place of chaos. Fog constantly covering every hole, ready to deceive the unwary to fall to maybe an inconvinient hole. 
#- Or a quick and fiery death, and do be wary of the colour of the clouds - When they take a dark, gray tone. You can assume that new vicious fiends are making their way to populate this island.
#- II: Pigmen - Pig-Kids§0
§0Pigmen appear to have once been human, due to their shape, and them having enough decency to cover their loins. But I assure you, they are not even worthy to be compared to an actual pig anymore, lost, tortured souls. probably paying
#- for a previous life of sin and heresy. They do seem to have reproductive activities, as infant variants of these creatures can be found. But are quite rare, as the weaker infants are eaten by the stronger ones. Only the most vicious of infants making it
#- to adulthood.§0
§0There does seem to be a hierarchy inbetween packs of Pigmen. As usually they can be seen following a Pigmen with an enchanted sword.§0
§0Leadership seems to be delivered with birth, as I have seen infants already holding enchanted swords.
#- These creatures are pushovers, even if vicious in large numbers. They are no threat to a decent fighter, and even then. You can avoid fighting them by just not attacking them first, they don't react to namecalling, bumping or staring.
#- 
#- III: Burnt.§0
§0A demon taken straight from the Nether. Placed on the surface of earth to cause chaos and madness.§0
§0They seem to be lonely creatures, as it's rare to find more than 1 in a same day. But they're not to be under-estimated.
#- They fire projectiles in quick succesion. So if not prepared, you can be taken down easily. After shooting, they go into a cooldown period, made evident by their flame going off and their height of levitation going lower. This time being optimal to attack
#- They're hostile creatures to anyone that isn't a fiend from the peninsula, and annoying as all hell. Do try to get rid of them, but with caution. Successfully taking one down grants a guaranteed blaze rod. So this place might be of interest to alchemists.
#- IV: Ghasts.§0
§0By far the rarest of creatures on this island, ever since I came to own this land, I've only seen one. But from what I can gather, they're not dangerous at all as long as you have good reflexes. They can  be noticed by their muffled moaning.
#- V: Slobber Witches§0
§0Cousins, sisters and nieces of the witches described in my book "Templar's Tale". They rely on potions both splash and regular to fight. When attacking usually throwing a slowness potion, followed by a posion potion
#- and then a damage one to finish you off.§0
§0When hit, they will quickly retreat to heal. Which is the best time to attack, assuming you can damage her faster than she can heal herself.§0
§0You can distinguish them by their nasty giggles when near.
#- VI: ???-man§0
§0I've seen this creature only twice. And it seems to be quite dangerous, so I halted investigation, looks like a regular enderman, and doesn't have a name-tag to make himself stand out, but as soon as he gets attacked. He quickly reveals -
#- - His true colours, teleporting in a quick, frantic fashion. As if it were raining, only to strike you from behind as soon as they get the chance.§0
§0They're vicious, and dangerous, they're not to be sparred with unless you know you'll win.
#- And if you don't think so, just avoid them, don't look at them, don't bump into them, don't come near them. And they'll do nothing to you aswell.§0
§0There's no way to distinguish one of these with a regular enderman as far as I can tell.
#- 